      <h2 parentName="article" {...{
        "id": "usebeforeunload"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="h2">{`useBeforeUnload`}</inlineCode></h2>
      <p parentName="article">{`This hook is just a helper around `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`window.onbeforeunload`}</inlineCode>{`.`}</p>
      <p parentName="article">{`On client side page transitions, Remix is aware of the current version of your app. If you deployed in the middle of a user's session on your site, the next time they click a link it will be a full page transition (as if you used `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`<a>`}</inlineCode>{` instead of `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`<Link>`}</inlineCode>{`) and then the user gets the freshest version of your site.`}</p>
      <p parentName="article">{`If you've got any important state on the page when this happens, you're going to want to save it off somewhere like local storage, because a real page transition will blow it away.`}</p>
      <p parentName="article">{`Remix or not, this is just good practice to do anyway. The user can change the url, accidentally close the browser window, etc.`}</p>
