          }}>{`}`}</span>{`
`}</code></pre>
      <p parentName="article">{`The `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`<Form>`}</inlineCode>{` component is how to perform data mutations like creating, updating, and deleting data. While it might be a mindshift to think about these tasks as "navigation", it's how the web has handled mutations since before JavaScript was created!`}</p>
      <p parentName="article">{`For an in-depth look at mutations with form, check out the `}<Link to="../mutations" mdxType="Link">{`Mutations`}</Link>{` page.`}</p>
      <h3 parentName="article" {...{
        "id": "form-action"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="h3">{`<Form action>`}</inlineCode></h3>
      <pre parentName="article" {...{
        "className": "language-js"
      }}><code parentName="pre" {...{
          "className": "language-js"
        }}><span parentName="code" {...{
            "className": "token operator"
          }}>{`<`}</span><span parentName="code" {...{
            "className": "token maybe-class-name"
          }}>{`Form`}</span>{` action`}<span parentName="code" {...{
            "className": "token operator"
          }}>{`=`}</span><span parentName="code" {...{
            "className": "token string"
          }}>{`"/projects/new"`}</span>{` `}<span parentName="code" {...{
            "className": "token operator"
          }}>{`/`}</span><span parentName="code" {...{
            "className": "token operator"
          }}>{`>`}</span>{`
`}</code></pre>
      <p parentName="article">{`This tells the form which action to call. The `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`action`}</inlineCode>{` export of the matching data module will be called. In the above example, the action url would match a file at `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`data/routes/projects/new.ts`}</inlineCode>{`.`}</p>
      <h3 parentName="article" {...{
        "id": "form-method"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="h3">{`<Form method>`}</inlineCode></h3>
      <pre parentName="article" {...{
        "className": "language-js"
      }}><code parentName="pre" {...{
          "className": "language-js"
        }}><span parentName="code" {...{
            "className": "token operator"
          }}>{`<`}</span><span parentName="code" {...{
            "className": "token maybe-class-name"
          }}>{`Form`}</span>{` method`}<span parentName="code" {...{
            "className": "token operator"
          }}>{`=`}</span><span parentName="code" {...{
            "className": "token string"
          }}>{`"post"`}</span>{` `}<span parentName="code" {...{
            "className": "token operator"
          }}>{`/`}</span><span parentName="code" {...{
            "className": "token operator"
          }}>{`>`}</span>{`
`}</code></pre>
      <p parentName="article">{`This determins the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
          "href": "https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Methods"
        }}>{`HTTP verb`}</a>{` to be used: get, post, put, patch, delete. The default is "get".`}</p>
      <p parentName="article">{`Native `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`<form>`}</inlineCode>{` only supports get and post, so if you want your form to work with JavaScript on or off the page you'll need to stick with those two. Without JavaScript, Remix will turn non-get requests into "post", but you'll still need to instruct your server with a hidden input like `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`<input type="hidden" name="_method" method="delete" />`}</inlineCode>{`. If you always include JavaScript, you don't need to worry about this.`}</p>
      <h3 parentName="article" {...{
        "id": "form-enctype"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="h3">{`<Form encType>`}</inlineCode></h3>
      <p parentName="article">{`Defaults to `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`application/x-www-urlencoded`}</inlineCode>{`, which is also the only supported value right now. Before 1.0 we'll also support `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`multipart/form-data`}</inlineCode>{`.`}</p>
      <h3 parentName="article" {...{
        "id": "form-replace"
      }}><inlineCode parentName="h3">{`<Form replace>`}</inlineCode></h3>
      <pre parentName="article" {...{
        "className": "language-tsx"
      }}><code parentName="pre" {...{
